pull_request.title: [android] Prevent random crashes in manage route
pull_request.body:
As reported in [Issue 10925](https://github.com/organicmaps/organicmaps/issues/10925), several crashes happen in the Manage Route functionality.

After some investigation, it looks like these _"Illegal State Exceptions"_ happen when updating the RecyclerView while it's computing a layout or scrolling, as described [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43221847/cannot-call-this-method-while-recyclerview-is-computing-a-layout-or-scrolling-wh).

This PR detects that situation and postpones the update of the RecyclerView to prevent crashes.

This PR implements the first version of the SpaceTraders UI application following the workplan specifications in `WORKPLAN.md` and `ShipAutomation.md`. The implementation successfully completes **Milestone M1** with a fully functional React-based dashboard.

## Key Features Implemented

### üöÄ Complete SpaceTraders API Integration
- Full API client with proper rate limiting (max 2 requests/second as required)
- Support for both Account Tokens (agent registration) and Agent Tokens (operations)
- Error handling with user-friendly messages
- Bearer token authentication following SpaceTraders v2.3.0 specification

### üì± Mobile-Accessible React UI
- Responsive design that works on both desktop and mobile devices
- Modern React with TypeScript and Vite build system
- Component-based architecture ready for React Native expansion
- Cross-platform storage abstraction using localStorage (ready for AsyncStorage)

### üéØ Core Dashboard Functionality
- **Agent Information Display**: Shows credits, headquarters, faction, and ship count
- **Fleet Management**: Visual overview of all ships with real-time status indicators
- **Ship Operations**: Basic actions including dock, orbit, and refuel with proper API calls
- **Token Management**: Secure storage and management of authentication tokens

### üõ† Technical Architecture
```
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/          # Reusable UI components (AgentInfo, ShipCard, TokenSetup)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ context/            # React context for token state management
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ screens/            # Main application screens (Dashboard)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ services/           # API client with rate limiting and error handling
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ types/              # TypeScript definitions for SpaceTraders API
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils/              # Storage, formatting, and utility functions
```

## Screenshots
The application includes:
1. **Token Setup Screen**: Clean interface for entering SpaceTraders agent tokens
2. **Main Dashboard**: Shows agent stats and fleet overview with ship action buttons
3. **Error Handling**: Graceful display of API errors and loading states

## Implementation Notes

- **Rate Limiting**: Implements proper 2 req/second limit to respect SpaceTraders API requirements
- **Security**: Tokens stored securely with proper redaction in logs
- **Error Resilience**: Comprehensive error handling with user feedback
- **Future-Ready**: Architecture supports upcoming milestones (M2-M7) and React Native integration

This establishes the foundation for all remaining features including contracts management, navigation, mining operations, market integration, and eventually the ship automation system described in `ShipAutomation.md`.

The app successfully demonstrates core functionality with real SpaceTraders API integration and provides a solid base for mobile APK generation as requested.

Fixes #3.

issue.title: [MVP P1] My Hand: fan layout with overlap and responsive scaling
issue.body:
Make the My Hand display feel like real cards.

Acceptance criteria:
- Cards rendered in a slight arc/fan with small overlap and z-order
- Scales down gracefully on narrow screens; wraps or shrinks width
- No layout jank on orientation or window resize
- Works in mock mode; no new dependencies unless necessary

Definition of done:
- Code, tests (golden or widget), and a short GIF in README/screenshots

comment.body:
Implemented the fan/arc layout for ‚ÄúMy Hand‚Äù with overlap, slight rotation, and responsive scaling. Wired into TableScreen and added a basic widget test.

Highlights:
- New `FanHand` widget (`lib/ui/widgets/fan_hand.dart`) lays cards in an arc with adjustable overlap and max angle; auto-scales to fit width.
- Table UI now uses `FanHand.builder` to render the hand while preserving legal/turn gating and existing slide animation.
- Added `test/fan_hand_test.dart` to confirm scaling and item building; full test suite green.
- README updated to mention the fan layout.

If you want a steeper arc or tighter overlap, I can tweak `maxAngleDeg`/`overlapFraction` defaults or expose a setting.

Refs: #1

issue.body:
### systemd version the issue has been seen with

257.6

### Used distribution

Nixos

### Linux kernel version used

6.16

### CPU architectures issue was seen on

x86_64

### Component

systemd-nspawn


### Unexpected behaviour you saw

When mounting a single file inside a symlink directory with idmap and privateUsers=pick, the container fail to start.

### Steps to reproduce the problem


mkdir /a/
touch /a/file
ln -s /a/ /b/
try to start the container with --bind(-ro or not)=/b/file:/b/file:idmap

### Additional program output to the terminal or log subsystem illustrating the issue

```sh
systemd-nspawn[54399]: Failed to map ids for bind mount /run/nixos-containers/.#machinename4719ff62fce7ecfc/a/single/file: Invalid argument
```

comment.body: After some search, this seems to be reasonable behavior, as bind mount should not follow symlink to prevent container escape. I'm was surprised by the error message before even getting that the file I want to mount is symlinked but I've found a workaround on my case (CF:https://github.com/Mic92/sops-nix/issues/719)
